        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 27 at 3:32PM CDT by NWS Midland/Odessa TX</headline>
        <description>At 332 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 14
miles northwest of Fort Stockton, moving northeast at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Imperial Reservoir and Firestone Test Track.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
